We have recommended the following:

Stop the practice of granting of additional cash advances to officials and/or employees with unsettled accounts;

Direct the Municipal Accountant to follow the prescribed procedures on the recording of cash advances and to make the necessary adjustments on the financial statements;

Ensure that grants of cash advances are properly supported with the necessary supporting documents to prove the necessity of the cash advances; and

Enjoin the concerned officers and employees to follow the relevant laws and regulations regarding the utilization and liquidation of cash advances.

We have reiterated our recommendation to require the municipal accountant to retrieve pertinent   vouchers/payrolls and, where necessary, prepare the reclassifying and/or correcting entries;

Set-up and maintain Subsidiary Ledgers showing detailed information on cash advances granted and liquidations per accountable officer/employee; and

Request for authority to write-off dormant unliquidated cash advances which remained non-moving for ten (10) years or more and where settlement could no longer be ascertained in accordance with COA Circular No. 2016-005 dated December 19, 2016.

We have recommended to require the BAC to complete documentation of all procurements to be made including the posting in PhilGEPS of the Notices of Award, Notices to Proceed and the Contract/PO and ensure that the printout copy of such posting is included among the supporting documents for payment of claims;

Require the Municipal Accountant to adopt measures to ensure compliance with the required documentation; and

Adhere strictly with Section 4(6) of P.D. 1445 and the rules and regulations of RA 9184.

We have recommended to require the concerned officers to submit all the required reports within the prescribed deadline and monitor compliance with the timely submission of reports;

Cause the suspension of payment of salaries of the concerned officials until they shall have complied with the requirements of the Commission in accordance with Section 122 of PD 1445; and

Fill out the vacant mandatory position of the Municipal Accountant.

