To thwart the happening of the above causes of untimely accomplishment of the LGU’s activities or to rectify, as a remedial measure on the noted deficiencies, we have recommended that management consider the following:

Direct the Municipal Engineer to prioritize and to fast tract the implementation of the LGU’s P/P/As;

Send a written demand to the contractors for the full and satisfactory performance of their obligations under their respective contract with the municipal government;

Enforce the provisions in the contract particularly the aspect on liquidated damages in congruence with the provisions on liquidated damages under RA 9184; and

Carefully and judiciously review and re-evaluate the necessary qualifications of the contractor as to its manpower compliment, financial capacity to undertake the contract, availability of the required heavy equipment for the contract and status of prior contract entered into by the supplier/contractor as to how satisfactory they were in their execution or performance of their obligation.

We have recommended to direct the designated Municipal Engineer to obtain the Certificate of Completion from the contractor and issue a Certificate of Inspection and Acceptance to support the recording of completed projects;

Require the Municipal Accountant to prepare Journal Entry Vouchers for the above listed projects to reclassify the amounts debited to due to NGA account to its appropriate infrastructure asset account. Henceforth, recognize projects under construction in the account Construction in Progress and transfer to appropriate Infrastructure Asset accounts upon completion; and 

Enforce the designated accountant to meticulously check completeness of the documentary requirements of all kinds of disbursements as prescribed under COA Circular No. 2012-001 in order to avoid disallowances in the future.

